cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this software in your research, please cite it as below.
type: software
title: hapax-refusals
abstract: |
  Refusal-as-data primitives extracted from the Hapax operating
  environment. Implements the surface-floored RefusalGate (R-Tuning
  post-emission verifier, Zhang et al. NAACL 2024 / arXiv 2311.09677)
  with calibrated per-surface posterior floors (0.60-0.90) and the
  refusal-as-data registry (append-only JSONL log of structured
  refusal events). Drop-in wrapper around any LLM emission point: the
  ``refuse_and_reroll`` helper turns a one-shot LLM call into a
  bounded re-roll loop that rejects below-floor or unmatched
  assertions and re-rolls with a stricter prompt addendum. Each
  rejection is recorded as data, not narrative — citable substrate
  for downstream calibration work.
